            "answer_text": "Scrolls are pieces of paper that had writings in them .i.e. Information, religious texts etcThen in 1398 Johann Gutenberg was born who  made the first (successfull) printing press and printed the first book( Gutenberg Bible).Since writing in scrolls was a tedious task people gradually started opting for printed books. Hence, the transition. (There were other attempts at printing but they were failures so didn't mention them). Hope this helps ",
